 <center><h2>Glacier Bear Guide</h2><br><br>I have successfully taken the glacier bear several times. The hardest <br>part is waiting for the first spawn. There is an 8 hour delay between <br>spawns.  Two ice bone skeletons serve as place holders for the bear. <br>I think the spawn is about 1 out of every three or four spawns is the <br>bear.  I have seen two bears spawn on more than one occasion. <br><br><br>Step 1)  Go to the glacier bear cave, and look for the wandering ice <br>bone skeletons and/or the bear (sense animals will find him if he's <br>there). If either of them are there, you are in luck. If it's the bear <br>great, if it is the wandering ice bone men (there are two of them) <br>that's still pretty good. <br><br><br>Step 2)  If you find the wandering ise bone skeletons, kill them both <br>(they are very, easy, easy green at lvl 35), and proceed to Step 4. <br><br><br>Step 3)  If you don't find the bear or the wandering ice bone men, <br>take a seat in the hallway half way between Sulon McMoor the evil <br>wizard (high 40's don't aggro him) and the little house where the ice <br>bone skeletons stand in place. Bring a deck of cards because you may <br>have a long wait (up to 8 hours). Once they spawn, they will walk out <br>of the room guarded by Sulon McMoor and come right past you. If you <br>are lucky, the bear will spawn instead of the ice bones. <br><br><br>Waiting there can be BORING.  There's no experience to be had and <br>nothing to watch or do in the cave.  On the other hand, if you go off <br>to play elsewhere, you may lose the spawn to someone else who is <br>camping it, and you'll never know if you did. <br><br><br>As an alternative to waiting, try making a pet, tell him to guard <br>here, and tell him to taunt.  Bind yourself to the area.  When you get <br>the message that your pet is taunting, gate back.  (I wish I had <br>thought of this when I was camping the bear.  Kudo's to the shaman who <br>came up with this idea if it works). <br><br><br>If you are low-mid 30's a good thing to camp while waiting are the icy <br>orcs and redwind who spawn at one of the ruined temples in Everfrost. <br>It is usually camped, which is good, because you won't be able to take <br>six orcs alone.  You can usually join a group there, or they will <br>agree to rotate orcs.  You should be able to solo an icy orc if <br>someone has broken the spawn. <br><br><br>Step 4)   After killing the ice bone spawn, camp, bind, go play a <br>twink, whatever.   Just write down the exact time and come back <br>exactly 7 hours and 50 minutes later (best to be a little early). <br>Sometimes the spawn can be late by as much as 20 minutes, don't <br>despair. If the ice bones spawn, kill them, and come back again 7 <br>hours 50 minutes later. Whatever you do, don't miss a spawn -- you've <br>already spent/wasted up to 8 hours getting it  timed. If you go to <br>sleep, set your alarm and make sure you are back in time (obviously, <br>this is best done over a weekend). Do this three or four times in a <br>row and you will absolutely get the bear this weekend. <br><br><br>I took out two bears together at lvl 34 with my pet (we were both <br>buffed to the max). Direct Damage does not work (as others have <br>indicated). Hit him  with disease and poisen spells and debuffs to <br>slow him down. <br><br><br>A druid who can wolf form you is good to have.  Sulon McMoor will not <br>aggro you if you are in wolf form and stay to the far side of the hall <br>from him.  The bear actually spawns in the cave Sulon is guarding, but <br>as he walks out on his own as soon as he spawns, I don't recommend <br>waiting there. <br><br><br>The bear also sometimes drop an enchanted ingot which is part of a <br>quest for a fairly awesome, cleric only, shield.  The ingot is no <br>drop.  If you have a good cleric friend, and you have the bear timed <br>right, you might want to bring him or her to get it.  You can also <br>hold the ingot, and go with your cleric friend to the Solusek Ro <br>temple to complete the quest.  After the cleric gives the NPC all but <br>one of the items, you give the bar to the NPC and then the cleric <br>gives the last item.  I have done this, and it does work. <br><br><br>Sincerely, <br>Oumgrok Shaman. <br>Level 42 ogre shaman <br>Innoruk Server <br><br><br><br><br></center><b><u>Zone Information:</u></b><br><br><a href='http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?zone=16'>Everfrost mob list</a><br>
<a href='http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/qsearch.html?zone=16'>Everfrost quest list</a><br><a href='http://www.eqatlas.com/everfrost.html'>Everfrost Map</a><br><form action='rate.php' method='post' name='rate'>
